content:
Here's a programmatically generated HTML code for a responsive 3-column table, meeting all your requirements:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Responsive Table</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        th, td {
            padding: 12px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        th {
            background-color: #4CAF50; /* You can choose any color */
            color: white;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        th, td {
            min-width: 120px; /* Ensures space for 10 alphanumeric characters */
        }
        td:first-child {
            text-align: left;
        }
        td:nth-child(2) {
            text-align: center;
        }
        td:last-child {
            text-align: right;
        }
        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            th, td {
                font-size: 14px;
                padding: 8px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Header 1</th>
            <th>Header 2</th>
            <th>Header 3</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Left Text 1</td>
            <td>Center Text 1</td>
            <td>Right Text 1</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Left Text 2</td>
            <td>Center Text 2</td>
            <td>Right Text 2</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Left Text 3</td>
            <td>Center Text 3</td>
            <td>Right Text 3</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **Table Layout:** The table is set to 100% width to occupy the full available space, making it inherently responsive.
- **Styling:** 
  - The `th` elements have a background color of `#4CAF50`, and text is in bold to differentiate header rows.
  - Padding is set to ensure the text is comfortably spaced within cells.
  - Minimum width for `th` and `td` is set to `120px` to accommodate at least 10 alphanumeric characters.
  - Text alignment is set accordingly: left for the first column, center for the second, and right for the third.
- **Responsive Design:** A media query adjusts the font size and padding for screens smaller than 600px, enhancing readability on smaller devices.
